Unofficial Translation by the Insurance Regulator of Cambodia

**Article 14 ..**

Individual insurance agent, who intends to renew the validity of the individual insurance agent registration card, shall make a request to **I.R.C.** within 3 (three) working days before the expiration date of the individual insurance agent registration card.

**Article 15 ..**

The **I.R.C.** shall not renew the validity of the individual insurance agent registration card for the individual insurance agent who:

- Did not serve as an insurance agent within the period of 180 (one hundred and eighty) days from the issued date of the individual insurance agent registration card, or
- Serve as insurance agent less than 180 (one hundred and eighty) days of the period of individual insurance agent registration card.

**Article 16 ..**

An individual, who intends to register in individual insurance agent register or to renew the individual insurance agent registration card, shall pay a fee of 40.000 (forty thousand) riels to the bank account of the **I.R.C.**..

**Chapter 3**

**Revocation of Individual Insurance Agent Registration Card**

**Article 17 ..**

**I.R.C.** shall revoke the individual insurance agent registration card in the following cases:

- Violate Law on Insurance and other relevant regulations and the provisions of this Prakas;
- Violate Code of Conduct of Individual Insurance Agent;
- Commit fraud or give advice to or take part with the clients to commit fraud in insurance sector;
- Give any false advices or improper services to the client;
- Premium diversion or increase a premium greater than the original premium;
- Become an incompetent person;
- Conduct any misdemeanor or felony.

**Chapter 4**

**Penalty provision**

**Article 18 ..**

Every individual insurance agent that violates the provision of this Prakas shall be subject to administrative sanctions by the **I.R.C.** as follows:

- Warning;
- Correction;
- Restriction on the approval or the registration;

